args: Crush Nanakusa?\nBut that's your family restaurant!
...Hey, who are these guys you're with?\nOne of them your boyfriend?
I don't even HAVE a boyfriend! They're just\nsome friends who've been helping me out!
Anyway, my culinary conquest\nhas already begun.
Don't be too surprised when I\ntake the world by storm, 'kay?
Ergh. Sorry you had to see that.
Oh, don't mind us. What I'd like to know is\nwhy Nazuna would want to take down the\nrestaurant she was basically raised in.
I have no idea. We trained there\nside-by-side back in the day.
After my father passed, she left home and\nopened the first Seven Leaves location.
It specialized in fast, inexpensive food\nthat refused to compromise on quality—\na far cry from Nanakusa's M.O.
She even went so far as to\nmake the place's catchphrase\n＂The true successor to Nanakusa.＂
Heh. So the little mogul-to-be ducked\nout and opened up her own joint, eh?
Yeah, and ended up poaching a big portion\nof Nanakusa's clientele in the process.\nThat's partially why we've been in a slump.
Aha. I think I'm startin' ta get the picture.
Mhm. Although the whole family really\njust wanted her to come back to us.
Nazuna... What are you planning, sis?
A few days later...\nAt Valerio's restaurant, Primula Julian
Aaagh, sweet cordon bleu!\nHelp me! HELP ME, RIVALS!
Picaro, huh? You have five seconds.\n...Aaand time's up. Get home safe. Bye.
So cold—like dry ice! My heart, she aches!\nAnd I will not be going anywhere, good sir!
I have come with a job! I wish for you to\nmake me some food—for L'Amandier!
Yeah, because as a PROFESSIONAL CHEF,\nfood must be reeeal hard to come by.

Just listen! My beloved L'Amandier is
on the cusp of being stolen from me!
Usurped! Absconded! And the culprit is
that Seven Leaves SLOP HOUSE!
Wait, did you just say Seven Leaves?
Tch... They're finally taking over here too,\nhuh?

That chain bought up every restaurant in
my hometown and turned them into
Seven Leaves franchised locations. The
owner's a pretty shrewd businessperson.
What?! That Nazuna girl who came\nto my restaurant is your SISTER?!
All the more reason for you to do\nsomething about this! Cook! For! Me!
Seriously, man, you're a chef.\nShouldn't you do that yourself?
I made an agreement with Nazuna!
It matters not how much you offer me—\nthis restaurant, much like my dignity,\nis NOT FOR SALE!
Listen, your employees have already\njumped ship. They're working for me now.\nYou're struggling in vain here.

This establishment is my home,
passed down from father to son, 
just as I shall one day pass it to mine!
It is my dream. I will NEVER give it up!
Hmm... How about a little test,\nthen? We'll see if that passion\nis enough to keep your shop afloat.
If you can make creative cuisine better\nthan one of my own chefs, I'll give up\non claiming your establishment.
It'll be an honest cook-off. Sound good?
So you agreed to a cooking battle\nwith your very restaurant as the prize.
I am quite aware my own cuisine will fall\nflat, but I had no choice but to accept\nthe challenge! I cannot lose my bistro!
I admit, I understand how you feel.\nAnd it's not like this doesn't concern me...\nFine. I'll help you out.
Valerio, you'll pitch in too, right?

Need I remind you who helped YOU
out when you were getting ready to
open this place?
*cough* Mitsuba! *cough*
Tch... Fine, I guess I should.
OHO HO! Victory is as good as mine!
The battle is in three days' time.\nIf we lose, Picaro must immediately\nsurrender L'Amandier.
Three days, huh? Not a lot of time.\nLet's get brainstorming on a menu, then.
I have just the idea! We'll start with—
Go make yourself useful by getting the\nplace prepped and cleaned. And don't\neven THINK about butting in.
(You can't just rob someone of\ntheir dream like that, Nazuna...)
(As your sister, it falls to me to\nstop you...and stop you I shall!)
